The condition whereby an internal organ pushes its way out through a gap in the muscle wall of the belly can occur at a variety of places between the chest and hips. But often you might not even notice you have one, a leading patient information portal, according to Informed Health. A hernia doesn't always result in discomfort, but some hernias may cause pain, a burning feeling of a sensation of pressure. READ: Exercise for osteoporosis Weak stomach muscles and tissue make hernias more likely. Hernias can be exacerbated by heavy lifting, coughing or squeezing. Hernias are usually operated upon, with hospital surgery needed to push the organ back inside and close up the gap.